               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-221-person1943">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  BAILEY
               <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1943" type="surname" value="BAILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1943" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1943" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             RICHMOND. I am <rs id="t18300415-221-viclabel1226" type="occupation">engaged at the periodical press</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-221-victim1942 t18300415-221-viclabel1226"></join>. I was walking along the Strand with two friends, on the 27th of February - we turned up <placeName id="t18300415-221-crimeloc1227">Catherine-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-221-crimeloc1227" type="placeName" value="Catherine-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-221-crimeloc1227" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-221-off1224 t18300415-221-crimeloc1227"></join>; it was about six o'clock in the evening - the Police-constable came and asked if any of us had lost our pocket-handkerchiefs; I felt, and said mine was gone - he requested us to wait, and, in about a minute and a half or two minutes, he brought the prisoner, and asked if I should know my handkerchief; I said Yes - we went to the watch-house, and I was asked if I had any mark on it; I said my family were very much in the habit of marking my things, and, on examining it, it had my mark and a number on it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-221-person1944">
                  JAMES 
                  VICKERY
               <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1944" type="surname" value="VICKERY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1944" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1944" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Brydges-street, and saw the prisoner walking up Catherine-street, with two others; a gentleman desired me to look sharp after them - they were following the prosecutor and his two friends; I went on the other side, and in a few minutes I saw the prisoner with this handkerchief in his hand; I desired them to wait- I went and took this handkerchief from the prisoner's pocket.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HEATON. Q. What first attracted your attention to the prisoner? A. A gentleman<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150102"></xptr>told me he thought they were very bad characters; I never saw the prisoner before - they were walking close behind the prosecutor; the prisoner said he had picked it up.</p>
               <p>MR. RICHMOND. This is my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had you used it just before? Yes - I am in the habit of carrying it in my hand, and, from the state of the evening, I am confident I must have used it within two or three minutes; it was not then in my hand, and it might possibly have dropped out of my pocket - I had had it in my hand in passing from the Sun newspaper-office; I cannot say how it left my person.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking up Russell-street with two young men, and found the handkerchief - it was dirty; I took it up and put it into my pocket - I went down York-street, and as I returned, the officer took me and another young man; I was above two hundred yards from the place where they say this was committed, and it is not likely I should have returned.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-221-person1945">
                  JAMES 
                  VICKERY
               <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1945" type="surname" value="VICKERY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1945" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-person1945" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw him with it his hand, not more than one yard from the prosecutor.</p>

               <p>GUILTY. Aged 17. - <rs id="t18300415-221-punish1228" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-221-punish1228" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-221-defend1940 t18300415-221-punish1228"></join>
               Confined Six Months
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
